div.p:
Mr John Cotton of New-England, in his Exposition of the seven Vials, upon the fifth of them understands the seat of the Beast to be Episcopal Government, and the whole Church of Scotland toMr John Cotton his pouring out of the seven Vials; the fifth Vial, page 4 & 5 be the Angel that poureth forth that Vial;
who (saith he) hath been carryed along herein, not in a way of popular Tumult, but with such Wisdom, Courage, Judgment, and Piety, that you may see and say, it is not a Vial poured out by an unadvised multitude, but by an Angel of God, by the heavenly Ministers of his Wrath: It hath been taken in hand with serious, and deep, and general Humiliation—and so seconded in their constant fruits of Reformation, as that their very Adversaries stand amazed to behold them.—Nor do I know that any of the former Vials have been poured out by any men, whose loyns have been more girt about with Truth, and whose clothing hath been more and white, then these servants of God have been girt and clothed withall.
Four Speeches in Guildhall 6 Octob. 1643 page 28, 29 30, 31, &c.
